definitions.definition: A placename ; any of several places:

subdefinitions.definition: A small village in Clapham cum Newby parish, North Yorkshire , England , previously in Craven district ( OS grid ref SD7270 ) .
A village and civil parish in North Yorkshire , previously in Hambleton district ( OS grid ref NZ5012 ) .
A village in Newby and Scalby parish, North Yorkshire , previously in Scarborough district ( OS grid ref TA0189 ) .

definitions.definition: An English habitational surname from Middle English for someone from one of these places.

main_definition: A placename ; any of several places:
secondary_definitions: ( countable ) An English habitational surname from Middle English for someone from one of these places.
